    h1 Toolbar Vue Component
    ul.docs-index
    p Toolbar is a fixed (with Fixed and Through layout types) area at the bottom of a screen that contains navigation elements. Toolbar does not have any parts, just plain links inside
    p Toolbar Vue component represents <a href="../docs/toolbar-tabbar.html">Toolbar</a> component.

    h2 Toolbar Components
    p There are following components included:
    ul
      li `f7-toolbar`

    h2 Toolbar Properties
    table.params-table
      thead
        tr
          th Prop
          th Type
          th Default
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="4") &lt;f7-toolbar&gt; properties
        tr
          td inner
          td boolean
          td true
          td When enabled (by default), it will put all the content within internal `toolbar-inner` element. Disable it only in case you want to put totally custom layout inside
        tr
          td position
          td string
          td
          td #[a(href="/docs/toolbar-tabbar.html#toolbar-position") Toolbar position], can be `top` or `bottom`
        tr
          td top
          td boolean
          td
          td Top positioned toolbar. Shortening for `position="top"`
        tr
          td top-ios
          td boolean
          td
          td Top positioned toolbar only for iOS theme
        tr
          td top-md
          td boolean
          td
          td Top positioned toolbar only for MD theme
        tr
          td top-aurora
          td boolean
          td
          td Top positioned toolbar only for Aurora theme
        tr
          td bottom
          td boolean
          td
          td Bottom positioned toolbar. Shortening for `position="bottom"`
        tr
          td bottom-ios
          td boolean
          td
          td Bottom positioned toolbar only for iOS theme
        tr
          td bottom-md
          td boolean
          td
          td Bottom positioned toolbar only for MD theme
        tr
          td bottom-aurora
          td boolean
          td
          td Bottom positioned toolbar only for Aurora theme
        tr
          td tabbar
          td boolean
          td false
          td Defines whether the Toolbar is also a Tabbar or not
        tr
          td labels
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables Tabbar with labels (affects only when `tabbar: true`)
        tr
          td scrollable
          td boolean
          td false
          td Enables scrollable Tabbar (affects only when `tabbar: true`)
        tr
          td no-shadow
          td boolean
          td
          td Disable shadow rendering for Material theme
        tr
          td no-hairline
          td boolean
          td false
          td Disable toolbar/tabbar top thin border (hairline) for iOS theme
        tr
          td hidden
          td boolean
          td false
          td Makes toolbar hidden

    h2 Toolbar Methods
    table.methods-table
      td
        th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-toolbar&gt; methods
      tr
        td .hide(<span>animate</span>)
        td Hide toolbar
      tr
        td .show(<span>animate</span>)
        td Show toolbar

    h2 Toolbar Events
    table.events-table
      thead
        tr
          th Event
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          th(colspan="2") &lt;f7-toolbar&gt; events
        tr
          td toolbar:hide
          td Event will be triggered when Toolbar becomes hidden
        tr
          td toolbar:show
          td Event will be triggered when Toolbar becomes visible

    h2 Toolbar Slots
    p Toolbar Vue component (`<f7-toolbar>`) has additional slots for custom elements:
    ul
      li `default` - element will be inserted as a child of `<div class="toolbar-inner">` element
      li `before-inner` - element will be inserted right before `<div class="toolbar-inner">` element
      li `after-inner` - element will be inserted right after `<div class="toolbar-inner">` element
    :code(lang="html")
          <f7-toolbar>
            <div slot="before-inner">Before Inner</div>
            <div slot="after-inner">After Inner</div>
            <!-- Goes to default slot: -->
            <f7-link>Left Link</f7-link>
            <f7-link>Right Link</f7-link>
          </f7-toolbar>

          <!-- Renders to: -->

          <div class="toolbar">
            <div>Before Inner</div>
            <div class="toolbar-inner">
              <a href="#" class="link">Left Link</a>
              <a href="#" class="link">Right Link</a>
            </div>
            <div>After Inner</div>
          </div>

